# UI-TARS-1.5-7B (Qwen2.5-VL) for the rig — Ollama Modelfile.
# Same two-FROM pattern as EvoCUA: language GGUF + vision projector (mmproj).
#
# IMPORTANT: you need a VISION-capable GGUF set — i.e. a repo that ships BOTH the
# LM gguf AND an mmproj-*.gguf. Text-only GGUFs (many mradermacher repos) will load
# but CANNOT see the screen. Known multimodal repos:
#   - Mungert/UI-TARS-1.5-7B-GGUF        (image-text-to-text; has mmproj)
#   - adriabama06/UI-TARS-1.5-7B-GGUF    (llama-cpp/multimodal; has mmproj)
# Pick a quant (Q5_K_M or Q8_0 both fit the 12 GB mobile 4080) and the f16 mmproj.
#
# Fill these two paths to the files you downloaded, then:
#   ollama create uitars-1.5-7b -f Modelfile.uitars
FROM ./UI-TARS-1.5-7B-Q5_K_M.gguf
FROM ./mmproj-UI-TARS-1.5-7B-f16.gguf

# 7B-Q5 + 16k ctx fits 12 GB with room (it's smaller than EvoCUA-8B-Q5, which already
# fit at num_ctx 16384). 16k holds history=4 of ~2k-vision-token frames with margin.
PARAMETER num_ctx 16384

# Sampling is also sent per-request by the adapter; these are load-time defaults.
PARAMETER temperature 0
PARAMETER top_p 0.9

# NOTE: do NOT override TEMPLATE. UI-TARS-1.5-7B is Qwen2.5-VL and ships a chat template
# in the GGUF; Ollama's /v1/chat/completions must apply it so multi-image user turns +
# system/assistant roles render correctly. The adapter supplies the full COMPUTER_USE
# prompt as the system message.
